# shadcn/ui Usage Guidelines

This project uses **shadcn/ui** for all UI elements and components.

## Configuration

shadcn/ui is configured in [components.json](mdc:components.json) with the following settings:
- Style: New York
- Base Color: Neutral
- Icon Library: lucide-react
- Components Path: `@/components/ui`
- Utils Path: `@/lib/utils`

## Adding Components

To add new shadcn/ui components to the project, use:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add <component-name>
```

Examples:
```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
npx shadcn@latest add card
npx shadcn@latest add input
```

## Initialization (if needed)

If shadcn/ui is not initialized in the project, use:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest init -d
```

## Guidelines

1. **Always use shadcn/ui components** for UI elements instead of building custom components from scratch
2. **Use the `cn()` utility** from [lib/utils.ts](mdc:lib/utils.ts) for conditional class merging
3. **Follow the component patterns** established by shadcn/ui for consistency
4. **Leverage Tailwind CSS** for styling customizations
5. **Use lucide-react icons** for all iconography needs

## Available Component Categories

- Form elements (Input, Select, Checkbox, Radio, etc.)
- Layout components (Card, Sheet, Dialog, Tabs, etc.)
- Navigation (Navigation Menu, Breadcrumb, Pagination, etc.)
- Feedback (Alert, Toast, Progress, Skeleton, etc.)
- Data display (Table, Badge, Avatar, etc.)
- Overlays (Dialog, Popover, Tooltip, etc.)

Always check the [shadcn/ui documentation](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components) for the latest components and usage patterns.
